YELLOW FEVER - BRAZIL (08)
**************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Wed 23 Jan 2008
Source: ChinaView, Xinhua News Agency report [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-01/24/content_7483265.htm>

The Brazilian authorities confirmed on Wednesday [23 Jan 2008] one
more death from yellow fever in the central state of Goias, bringing
to 9 the total of mortal cases of the tropical disease.
The victim was a guard of the Federal University of Goias. He has
been working in campus No. 2 close to a forest in the north of the
city of Goiania and was not vaccinated against yellow fever,
according to the Health Department of Goias.
The man, whose name was not revealed, died on 30 Dec [2007]. Medical
results of the Evandro Chagas Institute showed on Wed 23 Jan 2007
[established that the reason for his death was of yellow fever [virus
infection].
From last December [2007] to now, Brazil has already registered 9
deaths from yellow fever, including 7 in Goias, 2 in Brasilia, and
one in Parana.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[One hopes that with the aggressive yellow fever vaccination campaign
in Goias state, this will be the last human case of this disease.
An interactive HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Brazil can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=-10.8,-53.1,4>. - Mod.TY]
